title: For Sale:  Calico Liberty 1 9mm Carbine WITH 50 Round Magazine
postcontent:
I bought this as an impulse buy, it functions fine with the right ammo but can be picky, Fiocchi brand 9mm works flawlessly in my experience whereas Sellier & Bellot does not. I've put about 120 rounds through it. It is a Calico Liberty 1 carbine, it feeds from a unique helical magazine on top that holds 50 rounds. Spring for the magazine has a depress button to release tension for storage, then when loaded simply winds up 10 times and it's ready to go into the gun and fire. Internal design of this rifle is very similar to an MP5 as it is delayed blowback. Fairly accurate with some practice, fun plinker. Three position collapsible stock: closed, open, fully extended. Has front "kelly" grip installed. Grips are hollow and have removable caps on the bottom, the first grips cap fell off and I lost it, but I just ordered a new one plus a manual so if you buy it when they arrive in the mail I will give you the manual and cap free. The cap is purely cosmetic, doesn't effect function at all.

$850 cash, feel free to make me an offer, the worst I can say is no.

postcontent:
This is a cool revolver that I just don't need. It has been refinished and is in great shape with about 99% finish remaining as re-nickeled. The revolver was made in the 1920s, but looks like it could have been made last year. This is a 3 inch barrel Hand Ejector which is on the I Frame. The I frame is just a little bit smaller than a J Frame. The action is crisp, smooth, and tight. It would make a great carry gun, trail gun, or a SUPERB ladies gun.  The grips are customized from a set of 1960s Chief's Special grips, and are well fitted and quite attractive.

The action is pre-war S&W quality - smooth as silk and the lockup is tight as a bank vault. I have six rounds of .32 S&W Long ammunition that will go with it, so you will be ready to go as soon as you get it. 

I have sold my Smith & Wesson collection mostly all off in the past few months to pursue other collecting interests. It is about a third the price of a new one, and is frankly better built and nicer.

You will like it when you see it. This isn't some loose junker.
